{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_01M7NB1JEN9Q7xY755XsAg6L","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have all the context needed. Here is the complete implementation:\n\n---\n\n## File 1: `api/v1beta1/clusterpodplacementconfig_types.go`\n\nAdd the `MaxImageInspectionRetries` field to `ClusterPodPlacementConfigSpec` after the `FallbackArchitecture` field (line 58):\n\n```go\n// ClusterPodPlacementConfigSpec defines the desired state of ClusterPodPlacementConfig\ntype ClusterPodPlacementConfigSpec struct {\n\t// LogVerbosity is the log level for the pod placement components.\n\t// Valid values are: \"Normal\", \"Debug\", \"Trace\", \"TraceAll\".\n\t// Defaults to \"Normal\".\n\t// +optional\n\t// +kubebuilder:default=Normal\n\tLogVerbosity common.LogVerbosityLevel `json:\"logVerbosity,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// NamespaceSelector selects the namespaces where the pod placement operand can process the nodeAffinity\n\t// of the pods. If left empty, all the namespaces are considered.\n\t// The default sample allows to exclude all the namespaces where the\n\t// label \"multiarch.openshift.io/exclude-pod-placement\" exists.\n\t// +optional\n\tNamespaceSelector *metav1.LabelSelector `json:\"namespaceSelector,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// Plugins defines the configurable plugins for this component.\n\t// This field is optional and will be omitted from the output if not set.\n\t// +optional\n\tPlugins *plugins.Plugins `json:\"plugins,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// FallbackArchitecture defines the architecture to use if the image inspector cannot determine the image's architecture.\n\t// If configured, the PodPlacementController will set the node affinity of the pod to the fallback architecture\n\t// if the image inspector cannot determine the image's architecture.\n\t// +optional\n\t// +kubebuilder:default=\"\"\n\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=arm64;amd64;ppc64le;s390x;\"\"\n\tFallbackArchitecture string `json:\"fallbackArchitecture,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// MaxImageInspectionRetries is the maximum number of times the image inspector will retry\n\t// inspecting an image before giving up.\n\t// +optional\n\t// +kubebuilder:default=5\n\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=20\n\tMaxImageInspectionRetries *int32 `json:\"maxImageInspectionRetries,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe only change is adding the `MaxImageInspectionRetries` field block after `FallbackArchitecture`.\n\n---\n\n## File 2: `api/v1alpha1/clusterPodPlacementConfig_conversion.go`\n\nAdd a new annotation constant and handle round-tripping in both `ConvertTo` and `ConvertFrom`:\n\n```go\npackage v1alpha1\n\nimport (\n\t\"strconv\"\n\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/conversion\"\n\n\tmultiarchv1beta1 \"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/api/v1beta1\"\n)\n\nconst FallbackArchAnnotation = \"multiarch.openshift.io/fallback-architecture\"\nconst MaxImageInspectionRetriesAnnotation = \"multiarch.openshift.io/max-image-inspection-retries\"\n\n// ConvertTo converts this ClusterPodPlacementConfig to the Hub version v1beta1.\nfunc (src *ClusterPodPlacementConfig) ConvertTo(dstRaw conversion.Hub) error {\n\tdst := dstRaw.(*multiarchv1beta1.ClusterPodPlacementConfig)\n\n\t// ObjectMeta\n\tdst.ObjectMeta = src.ObjectMeta\n\n\t// Spec\n\tdst.Spec.LogVerbosity = src.Spec.LogVerbosity\n\tdst.Spec.NamespaceSelector = src.Spec.NamespaceSelector\n\t// Restore FallbackArchitecture from the annotation, if present.\n\t// This ensures the value is preserved across API version conversions.\n\tif arch, ok := src.Annotations[FallbackArchAnnotation]; ok {\n\t\tdst.Spec.FallbackArchitecture = arch\n\t}\n\t// Restore MaxImageInspectionRetries from the annotation, if present.\n\tif v, ok := src.Annotations[MaxImageInspectionRetriesAnnotation]; ok {\n\t\tif parsed, err := strconv.ParseInt(v, 10, 32); err == nil {\n\t\t\tval := int32(parsed)\n\t\t\tdst.Spec.MaxImageInspectionRetries = &val\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Status\n\tdst.Status.Conditions = src.Status.Conditions\n\n\t// +kubebuilder:docs-gen:collapse=rote conversion\n\treturn nil\n}\n\n/*\nConvertFrom is expected to modify its receiver to contain the converted object.\nMost of the conversion is straightforward copying, except for converting our changed field.\n*/\n\n// ConvertFrom converts from the Hub version (v1beta1) to this.\nfunc (dst *ClusterPodPlacementConfig) ConvertFrom(srcRaw conversion.Hub) error {\n\tsrc := srcRaw.(*multiarchv1beta1.ClusterPodPlacementConfig)\n\n\t// ObjectMeta\n\tdst.ObjectMeta = src.ObjectMeta\n\t// v1alpha1 does not have the FallbackArchitecture field.\n\t// Preserve the value in an annotation to avoid data loss during\n\t// v1beta1 -> v1alpha1 -> v1beta1 round-trip conversions.\n\tif dst.Annotations == nil {\n\t\tdst.Annotations = make(map[string]string)\n\t}\n\tif src.Spec.FallbackArchitecture != \"\" {\n\t\tdst.Annotations[FallbackArchAnnotation] = src.Spec.FallbackArchitecture\n\t} else {\n\t\tdelete(dst.Annotations, FallbackArchAnnotation)\n\t}\n\t// v1alpha1 does not have the MaxImageInspectionRetries field.\n\t// Preserve the value in an annotation to avoid data loss during round-trips.\n\tif src.Spec.MaxImageInspectionRetries != nil {\n\t\tdst.Annotations[MaxImageInspectionRetriesAnnotation] = strconv.FormatInt(int64(*src.Spec.MaxImageInspectionRetries), 10)\n\t} else {\n\t\tdelete(dst.Annotations, MaxImageInspectionRetriesAnnotation)\n\t}\n\n\t// Spec\n\tdst.Spec.LogVerbosity = src.Spec.LogVerbosity\n\tdst.Spec.NamespaceSelector = src.Spec.NamespaceSelector\n\n\t// Status\n\tdst.Status.Conditions = src.Status.Conditions\n\n\tif dst.Annotations == nil {\n\t\tdst.Annotations = make(map[string]string)\n\t}\n\n\treturn nil\n}\n```\n\nChanges: added `\"strconv\"` import, added `MaxImageInspectionRetriesAnnotation` constant, added restore logic in `ConvertTo`, and added preserve logic in `ConvertFrom`.\n\n---\n\n## File 3: `internal/controller/podplacement/pod_model.go`\n\nReplace the ha